My Gon compassionate as Just The bands of my confine-ment burst, Redeem’d my body from the dust, And bade my soul return:

Untir’d, his patience knows no bound, Amazing is his grace!

While three long years

Have roll’d their circles round,

I’ve stood a cumberer of the ground 3

Have oft provok’d him to his sace, And yet his mercy calle, and yet his wrath fot-bears.
